<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-30T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-30T02:00:00-05:00" n="166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.61/988: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Standley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-30T11:00:00+04:00">September
                                    30, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>829. Department’s 434, September 5, noon. Since Willkie has departed from
                            the Soviet Union without carrying on any further discussions relative to
                            the Polish situation in addition to those reported in my 380 of
                            September 2 [<hi rend="italic">26</hi>] from Moscow,<note n="75" xml:id="d166fn75">Not printed.</note> and in view of the good grace
                            with which Stalin is alleged to have received Willkie’s representations
                                <pb facs="0197" n="191" xml:id="pg_191"/> on behalf of the Poles, I
                            am of the opinion that it would be opportune to suggest to Mr. Churchill
                            through the Polish Government that the British Government take occasion
                            to supplement Willkie’s action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>